<div id="review_1356961762" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1356961762" />
    <a title="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel"><img alt="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613262129p2/25867535.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1356961762?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ " href="/user/show/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel">Carol She&#39;s So Novel꧁꧂ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780751517491" href="/book/show/22675.A_Morbid_Taste_for_Bones">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25867535-carol-she-s-so-novel?shelf=historical-crime-whodunnit">historical-crime-whodunnit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1356961762" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5638713107279252083">I read some of the Brother Cadfael books years ago &amp; found them just ok. May have been my age or (more likely) that this is a series that needs to be read in order. Clearly there is more to the good brother than his skills as a herbalist! No doubt more will be revealed about his past in later books.<br/><br/>I don&apos;t know anything about 12th century Wales or England, but certainly Peters had given the narrative &amp; dialogue a very authentic feel. &amp; monastery politics feels like modern office or school staffr</span>
  <span id="freeText5638713107279252083" style="display:none">I read some of the Brother Cadfael books years ago &amp; found them just ok. May have been my age or (more likely) that this is a series that needs to be read in order. Clearly there is more to the good brother than his skills as a herbalist! No doubt more will be revealed about his past in later books.<br><br>I don't know anything about 12th century Wales or England, but certainly Peters had given the narrative &amp; dialogue a very authentic feel. &amp; monastery politics feels like modern office or school staffroom politics &amp; gave me a sly chuckle!<br><br>The next one in the series <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/776384.One_Corpse_Too_Many__Chronicles_of_Brother_Cadfael___2_" title="One Corpse Too Many (Chronicles of Brother Cadfael, #2) by Ellis Peters" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1388239103s/776384.jpg" alt="One Corpse Too Many (Chronicles of Brother Cadfael, #2) by Ellis Peters" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a> sounds even more intriguing. I've popped that on my to read list.</span>
